I"s<h1 id="kubernetes">Kubernetes</h1>

<p>Kubernetes is the world’s most famous open-source container orchestration engine. It offers the ability to schedule and manage containers-Docker or otherwise-at scale. First, we will learn how to get a Kubernetes environment up and running, and understand the components. We will deploy a sample Kubernetes application and manage it with Kubernetes Dashboard. We will leave the most exciting part for the end; authentication and authorization.</p>

<h2 id="getting-up-and-running-mac-install">Getting up and running: Mac install</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Setup all prerequisites for minikube (Docker and Virtualbox)</li>
  <li>Setup and test Minikube</li>
  <li>Setup and test kubectl</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="setup-prerequisities">Setup Prerequisities</h3>

<h4 id="docker">Docker:</h4>

<ul>
  <li>Download links for Docker for Windows: <a href="https://www.docker.com/docker-windows"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Windows</code></a></li>
  <li>Download links for Docker for Linux: <a href="https://docs.docker.com/engine/installation/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Linux</code></a></li>
  <li>Download links for Docker for Mac: <a href="https://www.docker.com/docker-mac"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">Mac</code></a></li>
</ul>

<p>Command to test: <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">docker version</code></p>

